author: radu
msg: SLING-4406 - POJOs stored in the repository might not get recompiled when changed
* expanded POJO search to all possible paths from the repository such that the UnitChangeMonitor is queried
with the correct path of the POJO if the POJO is stored in the repository
* protected the UnitChangeMonitor against NPE if the queried paths are null

author: rhuijben
msg: In preparation for my following patch that improves obstruction detection
on update-move extend the 'svn info' output with some information about
text and property conflicts that is currently only shown when there is
(also) a tree conflict.
* subversion/svn/cl-conflicts.c
(svn_cl__get_human_readable_action_description): New function.
* subversion/svn/cl-conflicts.h
(svn_cl__get_human_readable_action_description): New function.
* subversion/svn/info-cmd.c
(print_info): Make sure the left and right version are logically
grouped by adding an header if there is a conflict but no tree
conflict.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/prop_tests.py
(dir_prop_conflict_details): Update expected result.
